        <div class="survival-card">
            <h1>Desert Survival Guide</h1>
            
            <div class="survival-section">
                <h3>Essential Tips</h3>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Water Conservation</h4>
                    <p>Carry at least 6 litres of water per person per day. Drink small amounts regularly rather than large quantities at once.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Sun Protection</h4>
                    <p>Wear loose, light-colored clothing, a wide-brimmed hat, and UV-protection sunglasses. Apply high-SPF sunscreen regularly.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Travel Timing</h4>
                    <p>Move during cooler morning and evening hours. Rest in shade during the hottest parts of the day (10am-4pm).</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="survival-section">
                <h3>Navigation</h3>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Using the Sun</h4>
                    <p>In the Northern Hemisphere, the sun will be in the southern part of the sky. A stick's shadow can help determine direction.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Night Navigation</h4>
                    <p>Learn to identify the North Star (Polaris) in the Northern Hemisphere for night navigation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="survival-section">
                <h3>Emergency Situations</h3>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Dehydration Symptoms</h4>
                    <p>Watch for dark urine, dizziness, fatigue, and dry mouth. These are early signs you need to rehydrate immediately.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="survival-tip">
                    <h4>Heat Stroke</h4>
                    <p>Recognize symptoms: hot/dry skin, confusion, rapid pulse. Cool the person immediately and seek help.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
